<item>
            <title>[LU-15540] How exclude usage on some OST from quota</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15540</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When mirroring files between 2 different pools, for example a ssd and hdd pool, both copies are counted against the users quota. Typically we only care about space on the hdd pool. If we turn off quota, at the ldiskfs, on the ssd pools could that be a simple work around for this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="68601">LU-15540</key>
            <summary>How exclude usage on some OST from quota</summary>
                <type id="9" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/issuetypes/undefined.png">Question/Request</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
