                            <resolved>Thu, 10 Feb 2022 16:05:52 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>Lustre 2.12.8</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="325875" author="paf0186" created="Thu, 10 Feb 2022 16:05:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This can be resolved by usage of the pool quotas feature in 2.14 and newer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="325775" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 9 Feb 2022 23:57:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mahmoud,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would not recommend that. &#160;It&#8217;s definitely not supported to have quota enabled on only some targets and would at least confuse some tools if not crash the system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a new feature, pool quotas, which can do exactly what you&#8217;re looking for by allowing different quota settings for different pools. &#160;It was released with Lustre 2.14 and will therefore be in the upcoming 2.15 maintenance release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
